<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 13 at 7:07PM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>A band of moderate snowfall is shifting east across the area.
Snowfall rates of an inch per hour are possible in this band. With
temperatures in mid 20s and now past sundown - accumulating snow
is possible on all untreated surfaces. Slippery conditions may
result.</description>
